Arrival delay over time

One point per arrival, graphed over duration of the train's service. Note seasonal trends, if applicable.

Arrival delay distribution

One bar per arrival time. Height counts the number of trains arriving at that time. This builds out the probability distribution of arrival times.

Trip progress

Start times are rebased onto January 2nd, 1970 (regardless of train's actual departure date), to stack their inineraries and highlight how arrival delays accrue over the trip.
